    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1887-10-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1887-10-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="485" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d485">
                <head>No. 30.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName> to Sir <persName type="to">L. S. Sackville
                                    West</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1887-10-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 22,
                                1887</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I had the honor of receiving last evening
                            your note of the 19th instant, conveying the instruction to you by the
                            Marquis of Salisbury that you should protest against the seizure of the
                            Canadian vessel <hi rend="italic">Alfred Adams</hi> in Behring Sea, and
                            against the continuance of similar proceedings by the United States
                            authorities on the high seas; and I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">T. F. Bayard.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
